1.title: Hotpots v Poptimists
1.plot: The Hotpots, a team from Lancashire, take on three pop music aficionados in the opening first round match of the fourteenth edition of the popular game show hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell.

2.title: Durhamites v LARPers
2.plot: A team consisting of three graduates from Durham University take on a trio of Live Action Role-Playing Game enthusiasts in the second contest from the first round of the quiz.

3.title: Pyromaniacs v Cartoonists
3.plot: Three players with a fervour for fire take on a team who are united by their appetite for animation in the third of the first round contests of the fiendish game show.

4.title: Motorheads v Time Ladies
4.plot: In this first round contest a trio of Formula One fans take on a team of three female Whovians. Hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell.

5.title: Birdwatchers v Dicers
5.plot: A trio of birdwatchers take on a team of boardgamers in tonight's opening heat. They compete to draw together the connections between things which, at first glance, seem utterly random.

6.title: Brews v Forrests
6.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts the series where knowledge will only take you so far. Patience and lateral thinking are also vital. A trio of tea drinkers square up to a family team in this opening heat.

7.title: Ancient Alumni v Three Peaks
7.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell presents the quiz show about making connections. Three graduates of Scotland's ancient universities take on the Three Peaks, a team with a passion for hill-walking.

8.title: Dragons v Westenders
8.plot: In the last of the initial first round matches Dragons, a team of Welsh descent, take on a trio of theatre fans in the challenging quiz show.

9.title: Hotpots v Durhamites
9.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts as first-round losers the Hotpots and the Durhamites return for one last chance at victory, to stay in this year's competition and to reach the second round.

10.title: Champion of Champions Special: Europhiles v String Section
10.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell asks the questions in a very special edition of the fiendish game show as series 9 winners the Europhiles take on series eleven champions the String Section.

11.title: Sport Special: Footballers v Korfballers
11.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts a one-off sports special of the game show as the Footballers and Korfballers return to compete against each other trying to identify the connections between seemingly unconnected things.

12.title: Family Special: Lasletts v Meeples
12.plot: Two teams made up of family members return for this special edition. Series 8 semi-finalists The Laslett family take on the Meeples team from series 13 that features Gail Trimble, her husband and her brother.

13.title: Quiz Special: QI Elves v Inquisitors
13.plot: The QI Elves and Inquisitors return for a very special one-off edition of the quiz. They compete to draw together the connections between things which, at first glance, seem utterly random.

14.title: Motorheads v Cartoonists
14.plot: Two teams of first-round losers, the Motorheads and the Cartoonists, return for one last chance to stay in the competition.

15.title: Birdwatchers v Brews
15.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts the game show in which patience and lateral thinking are crucial. Two teams of first round losers face each other for one last chance to stay in the competition.

16.title: Dragons v Three Peaks
16.plot: Two more teams of first round losers, Dragons and Three Peaks, battle it out for a final chance to stay in the competition. Hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell.

17.title: Poptimists v LARPers
17.plot: Two teams, the Poptimists and LARPers, that won their first round matches return to face each other in the opening match up of the second round. Each team will seek to find the connection between seemingly unrelated things.

18.title: Pyromaniacs v Time Ladies
18.plot: The Pyromaniacs and Time Ladies, two teams of first round winners go up against each other in this second round contest to determine who will progress to the next round.

19.title: Brews v Dicers
19.plot: The tea loving team Brews and the team of board-game players Dicers both won their first round matches and now meet in this second round tie in the challenging quiz show.

20.title: Ancient Alumni v Westenders
20.plot: Three graduates of Scotland's ancient universities, the Ancient Alumni, and a trio of theatre aficionados, the Westenders, both won their first round matches to meet in this second round clash.

21.title: Motorheads v LARPers
21.plot: A team of motor racing enthusiasts take on three live action role-players. Both teams have won a game and lost a game, so this is their last chance to stay in the tournament.

22.title: Durhamites v Pyromaniacs
22.plot: The Durhamites and Pyromaniacs return to face off. Both teams playing tonight have won a game and lost a game so this is their last chance to stay in the tournament.

1.title: Stewards v Parishioners
1.plot: The fiendishly difficult game show hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell returns for a thirteenth series. First up a team of J.R.R. Tolkien fans take on a church team.

2.title: Geocachers v Vikings
2.plot: A team of geocachers take on a trio from York in this opening round contest of the challenging game show show that seeks to find the connections between seemingly random things.

3.title: Snake Charmers v Extras
3.plot: A team of reptile lovers take on a team made up of TV and film background artists in another contest from the opening heats of this years brain-teasing competition.

4.title: Eco-Warriors v Escapologists
4.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts another heat from the opening round of the game show. This week a trio of environmentalists face a trio of friends who like to tackle escape rooms as a hobby.

5.title: Lapsed Physicists v Belgophiles
5.plot: In this opening round contest a trio of former physicists take on three people who united by their love of Belgium. Hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell.

6.title: Meeples v Tequila Slammers
6.plot: In this heat a team of board-gamers (led by University Challenge alumnus Gail Trimble) face three lovers of Latin cuisine. They will compete to draw together the connections between seemingly unconnected things.

7.title: Cricketers v Inquisitors
7.plot: In this edition of the popular game show a team of cricket fans will be tested as they face a team made up of three professional question setters. Hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell.

8.title: Wanderers v Pedagogues
8.plot: A team comprising of three solo applicants take on a trio of teachers in the latest opening heat of the fiendishly difficult game show hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell.

9.title: Disparates v Beaks
9.plot: In this opening heat a team of former strangers who met on a quiz app face a team comprising of three public school teachers. Hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell.

10.title: Dandies v Gaffers
10.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts another edition of the challenging quiz. A team of fashionistas take on a team of football coaches in this opening heat.

11.title: Arrowheads v Wombles
11.plot: A team of darts players take on a team made up of supporters of AFC Wimbledon in this opening round heat of the fiendish game show hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell.

12.title: Detectives v Theatricals
12.plot: In the last of the opening heats of the popular quiz a team made up of Sherlock Holmes fans take on three theatre workers. Hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell

13.title: Vikings v Parishioners
13.plot: Two winning teams from round one meet in this game. The Vikings, a team from York, face church team the Parishioners in the fiendish game show hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell.

14.title: Eco-Warriors v Snake Charmers
14.plot: Eco-Warriors, a team of environmentalists, return to face another trio that won through their first-round match - the reptile loving Snake Charmers. Hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell.

15.title: Meeples v Belgophiles
15.plot: The Meeples, a team of boardgamers, saw off Tequila Slammers in the opening round to set up this meeting with another winning side. The Belgophiles progressed at the expense of the Lapsed Physicists.

16.title: Wanderers v Inquisitors
16.plot: Two more teams that won through their first round matches meet in the next round of the connected quiz show as a team of solo applicants face a trio of question setters.

17.title: Dandies v Beaks
17.plot: Two more teams that won through the first round clash, as a team of fashion fans take on three public school teachers in the quiz that draws together connections between things.

18.title: Detectives v Arrowheads
18.plot: A team of Sherlock Holmes fans take on three darts players in this second round contest of the quiz show that seeks to find the connection between seemingly unconnected things.

19.title: Meeples v Parishioners
19.plot: Two teams that lost their second round matches return for their last chance to stay in the competition. The Meeples, a team of boardgamers face church team Parishioners.

20.title: Snake Charmers v Inquisitors
20.plot: Two more teams of round-two losers, the Snake Charmers and the Inquisitors, return for a last chance to stay in the competition. They compete to find the connections between things which seem random.

21.title: Dandies v Arrowheads
21.plot: Two teams that lost in the second round, a team of fashionistas, the Dandies, face the Arrowheads - a team of three darts players for one last chance to stay in the competition.

22.title: Cricketers v Escapologists
22.plot: Two teams of high-scoring losers return to compete for a last chance to stay in the competition as a trio of cricket fans take on three friends who enjoy tackling escape rooms.

23.title: Meeples v Inquisitors
23.plot: Two losing teams return for a final chance to stay in the competition as a team of boardgamers face a team made up of three professional question setters. Hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell.

24.title: Dandies v Escapologists
24.plot: Three dedicated followers of fashion, the Dandies, take on the Escapologists in a final chance to stay in the competition.

25.title: Eco-Warriors v Inquisitors
25.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts the first match from the third-round of the competition. A team of three environmentalists take on a team made up of question setters for a place in the quarter-finals.

26.title: Wanderers v Vikings
26.plot: This round-three game sees a team made up of solo applicants to the show, the Wanderers, return to face the team from York called the Vikings with a place in the quarter-finals at stake.

27.title: Detectives v Escapologists
27.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts this third round match-up between a team of three Sherlock Holmes fans and the Escapologists, three friends who enjoy tackling escape rooms.

28.title: Belgophiles v Beaks
28.plot: There is a place in the quarter-finals of the quiz hosted by Victoria Coren Mitchell at stake when the team that loves all things Belgian meets the team of public school teachers.

29.title: Wanderers v Eco-Warriors
29.plot: Two teams that lost their third round match return for a final chance to stay in the competition as the team of solo applicants take on the trio of environmentalists.

30.title: Detectives v Beaks
30.plot: Two more teams that lost in the third round return for one last chance to stay in the competition as the team of Sherlock Holmes fans take on the team of public school tutors.

31.title: Vikings v Inquisitors
31.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell presents the first of the quarter-finals as two third round winners, a team from York and a team of question setters, meet for a place in the semi-finals.

32.title: Belgophiles v Escapologists
32.plot: Two teams of third round winners return to battle it out for a place in the semi-finals in this quarter final match. The team that love all things Belgian face the trio who enjoy tackling escape rooms.

33.title: Detectives v Vikings
33.plot: Two teams of third round losers, the trio of Sherlock Holmes fans and the team from York, return for one last chance to reach the semi-finals of the quiz.

34.title: Eco-Warriors v Escapologists
34.plot: These two teams first faced each other in the fourth of the first round contests back in August 2017, now as third round losers they meet again for one last chance to reach the semi-finals.

35.title: Semi-Final 1
35.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts the first of the semi-finals as two returning teams compete by finding the connection between seemingly random things such as Wolf Man, Dora, Rat Man and Little Hans.

36.title: Semi-Final 2
36.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts the second semi-final of the competition as the final two returning teams do battle to see who can take their place in this year's final.

37.title: The Final
37.plot: Victoria Coren Mitchell presides over the grand final of the challenging quiz show. In this year's final the Escapologists meet the Belgophiles for the chance to win the coveted trophy.
